Program: Discovery
Title: Weathering the Storm - floods
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrys9
Last Broadcast Date: 28 September 2004
The third in a series on the world's extreme weather looks at the impact of floods. Bangladesh is situated on one of the world's largest potential flood plains, and indeed a sixth of the world's population live in an area which floods. A look at how Bangladesh is trying to become more prepared for future floods. Show less